{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17604361","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17604361"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:52:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:52:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15823"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15823","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15823"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.2,0.24,0.39,0.06,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8514"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114360"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8514","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8514"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15823"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96361"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"8618"},{"type":"tags","id":"8628"},{"type":"tags","id":"9847"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20436"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20452"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114360","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114360"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring cardiac development, the interatrial septum forms through the growth of two separate septa. The septum primum develops first, followed by a second septal structure.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the formation of the septum secundum?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Grows as a crescentic fold from the dorsal wall","Develops from the atrioventricular cushions","Forms from the ventral wall downwards","Extends upwards from the cardiac apex","Develops to the left of septum primum"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecrescentic fold from the dorsal wall\u003C/strong\u003E accurately describes the formation of the septum secundum. It grows downward from the roof of the primitive atrium, developing to the right of the septum primum.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eatrioventricular cushions\u003C/strong\u003E contribute to atrioventricular canal septation but not to the septum secundum. The septum secundum does not \u003Cstrong\u003Eform from the ventral wall downwards\u003C/strong\u003E as it grows from the dorsal (posterior) wall. It does not \u003Cstrong\u003Eextend upwards from the cardiac apex\u003C/strong\u003E since the atrial septa develop in the superior portion of the heart, and it does not \u003Cstrong\u003Edevelop to the left of septum primum\u003C/strong\u003E as it always develops on the right side.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe septum secundum is crucial in forming the foramen ovale with the septum primum, allowing right-to-left shunting of blood during foetal development. After birth, these septa fuse to form the fossa ovalis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The septum secundum forms as a crescentic fold from the dorsal wall of the primitive atrium during cardiac development.","The septum secundum develops to the right of the septum primum to form the interatrial septum.","The foramen ovale forms between the septum primum and septum secundum to allow right-to-left shunting in the foetus."],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96361"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15823"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},